Lamu squatters displaced bythe Shifta War of the 1960s want to be compensated by both the county and national governments.The 5,000 squatters from Kiunga, Manda, Rubu and Shanga met at the Lamu Fort yesterday to chart a way forward.The squatters also want to be settled at an alternative location.They also want a detailed report from the Truth Justice and Reconciliation Commission. The TJRC met squatters in 2012 and promised to release a report, but this is yet to be done.